column1: Most values are default encodings from Supreme Court Database. Marks0/1 indicates a case was a Marks/Plurality decision when = 1. Main is used to determine if an opinion is the main judgement of the Court easily. Missing  values for sentiment measures either mean the justice (row did not author an opinion) did not write an opinion or the opinion failed to extract in prior processing.
